## 4. System Architecture

### 4.1 High-Level Architecture

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                        USER BROWSER                         │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │
│  │         Devbase Studio (Next.js Web App)             │  │
│  │  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐  ┌────────────┐    │  │
│  │  │  Visual    │  │ Properties │  │   Code     │    │  │
│  │  │  Builder   │  │   Panel    │  │  Editor    │    │  │
│  │  └────────────┘  └────────────┘  └────────────┘    │  │
│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                            │
                            │ API Calls
                            ↓
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   BACKEND SERVICES                           │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │
│  │              Supabase (Backend)                       │  │
│  │  ┌────────┐  ┌────────┐  ┌────────┐  ┌────────┐   │  │
│  │  │Postgres│  │  Auth  │  │Storage │  │Real-time│   │  │
│  │  └────────┘  └────────┘  └────────┘  └────────┘   │  │
│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │
│  │              Code Generation Service                  │  │
│  │  (Next.js Generation, React Native Generation)       │  │
│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │
│  │              Deployment Service                       │  │
│  │  (Vercel API, Expo EAS, AWS CloudFormation)         │  │
│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                            │
                            │ Deploy
                            ↓
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   USER INFRASTRUCTURE                        │
│  ┌────────────────┐  ┌────────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐ │
│  │   Web App      │  │  iOS App       │  │ Android App  │ │
│  │   (Vercel)     │  │  (App Store)   │  │ (Play Store) │ │
│  └────────────────┘  └────────────────┘  └──────────────┘ │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │
│  │          User's AWS Account (Optional)              │  │
│  │  (S3, CloudFront, Amplify, CodeBuild, RDS, etc.)   │  │
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 4.2 Component Architecture

```
Devbase Studio Application
│
├── Frontend (Next.js 14 App Router)
│   ├── /app                        # Next.js App Router
│   │   ├── /builder               # Visual builder pages
│   │   ├── /projects              # Project management
│   │   └── /api                   # API routes
│   │
│   ├── /components
│   │   ├── /builder               # Builder-specific components
│   │   │   ├── Canvas.tsx        # Drag & drop canvas
│   │   │   ├── ComponentLibrary.tsx
│   │   │   ├── PropertiesPanel.tsx
│   │   │   └── LayersPanel.tsx
│   │   │
│   │   ├── /ui                    # shadcn/ui components
│   │   └── /modules               # Module UI components
│   │
│   ├── /lib
│   │   ├── /generators            # Code generators
│   │   ├── /functions             # Function library
│   │   ├── /modules               # Module definitions
│   │   └── /utils                 # Utilities
│   │
│   └── /store                      # State management (Zustand)
│
├── Backend (Supabase + Edge Functions)
│   ├── /database                   # SQL schemas
│   │   ├── tables.sql
│   │   ├── functions.sql
│   │   └── policies.sql           # RLS policies
│   │
│   ├── /functions                  # Supabase Edge Functions
│   │   ├── generate-code/
│   │   ├── deploy-app/
│   │   └── create-project/
│   │
│   └── /storage                    # Storage buckets
│       ├── user-uploads/
│       ├── generated-code/
│       └── module-assets/
│
├── Mobile (React Native + Expo)
│   ├── /app                        # Expo Router
│   ├── /components                 # React Native components
│   └── /lib                        # Shared utilities
│
└── Infrastructure
    ├── /terraform                  # Infrastructure as Code
    ├── /docker                     # Docker configs
    └── /.github                    # GitHub Actions
```

### 4.3 Data Flow

**1. Project Creation Flow:**

```
User creates project
    ↓
Frontend validates input
    ↓
API call to Supabase
    ↓
Create project record in DB
    ↓
Initialize Git repository
    ↓
Create default file structure
    ↓
Return project ID to frontend
    ↓
Redirect to builder
```

**2. Component Drag & Drop Flow:**

```
User drags component from library
    ↓
React DnD handles drag state
    ↓
User drops on canvas
    ↓
Calculate position (x, y)
    ↓
Generate unique component ID
    ↓
Add to project state (Zustand)
    ↓
Render component on canvas
    ↓
Auto-save to Supabase (debounced)
    ↓
Git auto-commit (background)
```

**3. Module Installation Flow:**

```
User clicks "Install Module"
    ↓
Fetch module definition from DB
    ↓
Check dependencies
    ↓
Show installation wizard
    ↓
User configures module settings
    ↓
Execute installation:
  - Add database tables (SQL)
  - Register API endpoints
  - Add components to library
  - Install npm packages
  - Update project config
    ↓
Show success message
    ↓
Update UI to show module components
```

**4. Function Attachment Flow:**

```
User selects component
    ↓
Opens Properties Panel
    ↓
Clicks "Attach Function"
    ↓
Browse function library
    ↓
Select function (e.g., "Get User Location")
    ↓
Configure function parameters
    ↓
Define onSuccess/onFailure actions
    ↓
Save function attachment
    ↓
Generate event handler code
    ↓
Update component definition
```

**5. Publish Flow:**

```
User clicks "Publish"
    ↓
Show pre-publish checklist
    ↓
Run validation:
  - Check required configs
  - Validate component tree
  - Check API endpoints
    ↓
Start deployment process:
  ├─→ Generate Next.js code
  ├─→ Generate React Native code
  ├─→ Generate API endpoints
  └─→ Generate database migrations
    ↓
Commit to Git
    ↓
Deploy in parallel:
  ├─→ Web: Deploy to Vercel
  │   └─→ Build → Deploy → Get URL
  │
  └─→ Mobile: Check for native changes
      ├─→ Native changes? → Full build
      │   ├─→ Build iOS (EAS)
      │   ├─→ Build Android (EAS)
      │   └─→ Notify user (submit to stores)
      │
      └─→ JS only? → OTA update
          └─→ Push update → Live in 30s
    ↓
Show success with URLs
    ↓
Send notification to user
```

### 4.4 Security Architecture

**Authentication Flow:**

```
User opens Devbase Studio
    ↓
Check for existing session
    ├─→ Valid session → Load builder
    └─→ No session → Show login
        ↓
        User chooses auth method:
        ├─→ OAuth (Google/GitHub/etc.)
        │   └─→ Redirect to provider
        │       └─→ Callback with token
        │           └─→ Exchange for JWT
        │
        ├─→ Magic Link
        │   └─→ Send email
        │       └─→ Click link
        │           └─→ Create session
        │
        └─→ Email/Password
            └─→ Verify credentials
                └─→ Create session
    ↓
Store JWT in httpOnly cookie
    ↓
Set refresh token
    ↓
Load user profile
    ↓
Redirect to builder
```

**Authorization (Row Level Security):**

```sql
-- Example RLS policy for projects table
CREATE POLICY "Users can only access their own projects"
  ON projects
  FOR ALL
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id);

-- Example RLS for shared projects
CREATE POLICY "Users can access shared projects"
  ON projects
  FOR SELECT
  USING (
    auth.uid() = user_id OR
    auth.uid() IN (
      SELECT collaborator_id
      FROM project_collaborators
      WHERE project_id = projects.id
    )
  );
```

