### 6.2 Module System

**6.2.1 Module Structure**

Each module must include:

```typescript
interface Module {
  // Metadata
  id: string;
  name: string;
  version: string;
  description: string;
  author: string;
  license: string;
  
  // Dependencies
  dependencies: {
    modules?: string[];        // Other modules
    packages?: Record<string, string>; // npm packages
    functions?: string[];      // Required functions
  };
  
  // Assets
  components: Component[];     // React components
  hooks: Hook[];              // React hooks
  database: {
    schema: string;           // SQL schema
    migrations: Migration[];  // Database migrations
    seeds?: Seed[];          // Test data
  };
  api: APIEndpoint[];         // Backend endpoints
  mobile: {
    screens: Screen[];        // React Native screens
    navigation: Navigation;   // Navigation config
  };
  
  // Configuration
  config: ConfigSchema;       // User-configurable options
  
  // Documentation
  readme: string;             // README.md content
  examples: Example[];        // Usage examples
  changelog: string;          // CHANGELOG.md content
}
```

**6.2.2 Module Installation**

**Process:**
1. User browses module library
2. Clicks "Install"
3. System checks dependencies
4. Shows configuration wizard
5. User configures module settings
6. System executes installation:
   - Creates database tables
   - Registers API endpoints
   - Adds components to library
   - Installs npm packages
   - Updates project config
7. Shows success message with next steps

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Installation completes in < 30 seconds
- Rollback on any error
- Clear error messages
- Progress indicator
- Confirmation dialog for breaking changes

**6.2.3 Module Marketplace**

**Requirements:**
- Browse all modules
- Search and filter
- Sort by: Popular, Recent, Rating
- Module cards showing:
  - Name, description, icon
  - Author, version
  - Install count, rating
  - Last updated
  - Tags/categories
- Module detail page:
  - Full description
  - Screenshots/demo
  - Documentation
  - Reviews and ratings
  - Changelog
  - Source code link (if open source)
  - Install button

