## 11. Deployment System

### 11.1 Deployment Architecture

```
Deployment Pipeline:

User Clicks "Publish"
    ↓
Pre-deployment Checks
    ├─→ Validate project
    ├─→ Check environment variables
    └─→ Run tests (if configured)
    ↓
Generate Code
    ├─→ Web (Next.js)
    ├─→ Mobile (React Native)
    └─→ Database (SQL)
    ↓
Git Commit & Push
    ↓
Deploy in Parallel
    ├─→ Web Deploy (Vercel)
    │   └─→ Build → Deploy → Get URL
    │
    └─→ Mobile Deploy
        ├─→ Detect changes
        │   ├─→ Native code changed?
        │   │   ├─→ Yes: Full build (EAS)
        │   │   │   ├─→ iOS build (5-15 min)
        │   │   │   └─→ Android build (5-15 min)
        │   │   └─→ No: OTA update (30 sec)
        │   │       └─→ Push JS bundle
        │
    ↓
Post-deployment
    ├─→ Run smoke tests
    ├─→ Update deployment record
    ├─→ Send notifications
    └─→ Show success message with URLs
```

### 11.2 Vercel Integration

```typescript
class VercelDeployer {
  async deploy(project: ProjectDefinition): Promise<DeploymentResult> {
    // 1. Generate code
    const code = await generateWebCode(project);
    
    // 2. Create/update Vercel project
    const vercelProject = await this.ensureProject(project);
    
    // 3. Upload files
    const files = await this.uploadFiles(code);
    
    // 4. Create deployment
    const deployment = await this.createDeployment({
      project: vercelProject.id,
      files,
      env: project.settings.environment,
      target: project.settings.deployment.target // production or preview
    });
    
    // 5. Wait for build to complete
    await this.waitForDeployment(deployment.id);
    
    return {
      success: true,
      url: deployment.url,
      deploymentId: deployment.id
    };
  }
  
  private async ensureProject(project: ProjectDefinition) {
    const existing = await this.findProject(project.id);
    if (existing) return existing;
    
    return await this.createProject({
      name: project.metadata.name,
      framework: 'nextjs',
      gitRepository: project.settings.git?.repository
    });
  }
}
```

### 11.3 Mobile Deployment (Expo)

```typescript
class ExpoDeployer {
  async deploy(project: ProjectDefinition): Promise<MobileDeploymentResult> {
    // 1. Generate React Native code
    const code = await generateMobileCode(project);
    
    // 2. Detect changes
    const hasNativeChanges = await this.detectNativeChanges(code);
    
    if (hasNativeChanges) {
      // Full build required
      return await this.fullBuild(project, code);
    } else {
      // OTA update
      return await this.otaUpdate(project, code);
    }
  }
  
  private async detectNativeChanges(code: GeneratedCode): Promise<boolean> {
    // Check if native code changed
    const nativePaths = [
      'android/',
      'ios/',
      'app.json',
      'package.json' // Check for new native dependencies
    ];
    
    for (const path of nativePaths) {
      if (await this.hasChanges(path)) {
        return true;
      }
    }
    
    return false;
  }
  
  private async fullBuild(
    project: ProjectDefinition,
    code: GeneratedCode
  ): Promise<MobileDeploymentResult> {
    // Build iOS and Android in parallel
    const [iosResult, androidResult] = await Promise.all([
      this.buildIOS(project, code),
      this.buildAndroid(project, code)
    ]);
    
    return {
      type: 'full-build',
      ios: {
        buildId: iosResult.id,
        downloadUrl: iosResult.url,
        status: iosResult.status
      },
      android: {
        buildId: androidResult.id,
        downloadUrl: androidResult.url,
        status: androidResult.status
      }
    };
  }
  
  private async otaUpdate(
    project: ProjectDefinition,
    code: GeneratedCode
  ): Promise<MobileDeploymentResult> {
    // 1. Build JS bundle
    const bundle = await this.buildBundle(code);
    
    // 2. Upload to Expo's CDN
    const uploadResult = await this.uploadBundle(bundle);
    
    // 3. Create update manifest
    await this.createUpdateManifest({
      projectId: project.id,
      bundleUrl: uploadResult.url,
      metadata: {
        version: project.metadata.version,
        timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
      }
    });
    
    return {
      type: 'ota-update',
      status: 'live',
      updateId: uploadResult.id
    };
  }
  
  private async buildIOS(
    project: ProjectDefinition,
    code: GeneratedCode
  ): Promise<BuildResult> {
    return await this.easClient.build({
      platform: 'ios',
      profile: 'production',
      projectDir: code.mobile,
      credentials: project.settings.deployment.ios
    });
  }
}
```

### 11.4 AWS Deployment (Optional)

```typescript
class AWSDeployer {
  async deploy(project: ProjectDefinition): Promise<AWSDeploymentResult> {
    // 1. Ensure CloudFormation stack exists
    await this.ensureStack(project);
    
    // 2. Generate code
    const code = await generateCode(project);
    
    // 3. Deploy web to S3 + CloudFront
    const webDeployment = await this.deployWeb(code.web, project);
    
    // 4. Deploy API to Lambda
    const apiDeployment = await this.deployAPI(code.api, project);
    
    // 5. Update database
    await this.updateDatabase(code.database, project);
    
    return {
      web: {
        url: webDeployment.url,
        cloudFrontDistribution: webDeployment.distributionId
      },
      api: {
        url: apiDeployment.url,
        functions: apiDeployment.functionNames
      }
    };
  }
  
  private async ensureStack(project: ProjectDefinition) {
    const stackName = `devbase-${project.id}`;
    
    try {
      await this.cloudFormation.describeStacks({
        StackName: stackName
      });
      
      // Stack exists, update it
      await this.updateStack(stackName, project);
    } catch (error: any) {
      if (error.code === 'ValidationError') {
        // Stack doesn't exist, create it
        await this.createStack(stackName, project);
      } else {
        throw error;
      }
    }
  }
}
```

---

## 12. Database Architecture

### 12.1 Supabase Schema

**Core Tables:**

```sql
-- Projects
CREATE TABLE projects (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users NOT NULL,
  name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  ui_kit VARCHAR(50) DEFAULT 'modern-minimalist',
  definition JSONB NOT NULL, -- Full project definition
  status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'active', -- active, archived, deleted
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  last_deployed_at TIMESTAMPTZ
);

-- Project Collaborators
CREATE TABLE project_collaborators (
  project_id UUID REFERENCES projects ON DELETE CASCADE,
  user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users ON DELETE CASCADE,
  role VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'editor', -- owner, editor, viewer
  added_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  PRIMARY KEY (project_id, user_id)
);

-- Modules
CREATE TABLE modules (
  id VARCHAR(50) PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  category VARCHAR(50),
  author VARCHAR(100),
  version VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
  definition JSONB NOT NULL,
  published BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
  downloads INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  rating FLOAT DEFAULT 0,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Installed Modules
CREATE TABLE project_modules (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  project_id UUID REFERENCES projects ON DELETE CASCADE,
  module_id VARCHAR(50) REFERENCES modules,
  version VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
  config JSONB, -- Module configuration
  installed_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Functions
CREATE TABLE functions (
  id VARCHAR(50) PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  category VARCHAR(50),
  author VARCHAR(100),
  version VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
  definition JSONB NOT NULL,
  published BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
  usage_count INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Deployments
CREATE TABLE deployments (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  project_id UUID REFERENCES projects ON DELETE CASCADE,
  user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users NOT NULL,
  type VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL, -- web, mobile-ota, mobile-full
  status VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'pending', -- pending, building, success, failed
  environment VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'production', -- production, staging, preview
  web_url TEXT,
  ios_build_id VARCHAR(100),
  android_build_id VARCHAR(100),
  error_message TEXT,
  metadata JSONB,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  completed_at TIMESTAMPTZ
);

-- User Settings
CREATE TABLE user_settings (
  user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY REFERENCES auth.users ON DELETE CASCADE,
  theme VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'light', -- light, dark, system
  notifications JSONB DEFAULT '{"email": true, "push": false}'::jsonb,
  preferences JSONB,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Activity Log
CREATE TABLE activity_log (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users,
  project_id UUID REFERENCES projects ON DELETE CASCADE,
  action VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  details JSONB,
  ip_address INET,
  user_agent TEXT,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Indexes
CREATE INDEX idx_projects_user_id ON projects(user_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_projects_status ON projects(status);
CREATE INDEX idx_project_collaborators_user_id ON project_collaborators(user_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_project_modules_project_id ON project_modules(project_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_deployments_project_id ON deployments(project_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_deployments_status ON deployments(status);
CREATE INDEX idx_activity_log_user_id ON activity_log(user_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_activity_log_project_id ON activity_log(project_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_activity_log_created_at ON activity_log(created_at DESC);

-- Full text search
CREATE INDEX idx_modules_search ON modules USING GIN(to_tsvector('english', name || ' ' || description));
CREATE INDEX idx_functions_search ON functions USING GIN(to_tsvector('english', name || ' ' || description));
```

### 12.2 Row Level Security (RLS)

```sql
-- Enable RLS
ALTER TABLE projects ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE project_collaborators ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE project_modules ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE deployments ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE user_settings ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE activity_log ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- Projects: Users can only access their own projects or shared projects
CREATE POLICY "Users can view their own projects"
  ON projects FOR SELECT
  USING (
    auth.uid() = user_id OR
    auth.uid() IN (
      SELECT collaborator_id
      FROM project_collaborators
      WHERE project_id = projects.id
    )
  );

CREATE POLICY "Users can create projects"
  ON projects FOR INSERT
  WITH CHECK (auth.uid() = user_id);

CREATE POLICY "Users can update their own projects"
  ON projects FOR UPDATE
  USING (
    auth.uid() = user_id OR
    auth.uid() IN (
      SELECT collaborator_id
      FROM project_collaborators
      WHERE project_id = projects.id
        AND role IN ('owner', 'editor')
    )
  );

CREATE POLICY "Users can delete their own projects"
  ON projects FOR DELETE
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id);

-- Collaborators
CREATE POLICY "Users can view collaborators of their projects"
  ON project_collaborators FOR SELECT
  USING (
    auth.uid() IN (
      SELECT user_id FROM projects WHERE id = project_id
    ) OR
    auth.uid() = user_id
  );

CREATE POLICY "Project owners can manage collaborators"
  ON project_collaborators FOR ALL
  USING (
    auth.uid() IN (
      SELECT user_id FROM projects WHERE id = project_id
    )
  );

-- Deployments
CREATE POLICY "Users can view deployments of their projects"
  ON deployments FOR SELECT
  USING (
    auth.uid() IN (
      SELECT user_id FROM projects WHERE id = project_id
    ) OR
    auth.uid() IN (
      SELECT collaborator_id FROM project_collaborators
      WHERE project_id = deployments.project_id
    )
  );

CREATE POLICY "Users can create deployments for their projects"
  ON deployments FOR INSERT
  WITH CHECK (
    auth.uid() IN (
      SELECT user_id FROM projects WHERE id = project_id
    ) OR
    auth.uid() IN (
      SELECT collaborator_id FROM project_collaborators
      WHERE project_id = deployments.project_id
        AND role IN ('owner', 'editor')
    )
  );

-- User Settings
CREATE POLICY "Users can manage their own settings"
  ON user_settings FOR ALL
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id);

-- Activity Log
CREATE POLICY "Users can view their own activity"
  ON activity_log FOR SELECT
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id);
```

---

## 13. Security Requirements

### 13.1 Authentication

**Requirements:**
- OAuth 2.0 support (Google, GitHub, Facebook, Apple, Microsoft)
- Magic link authentication (passwordless)
- Email/password with strong password requirements
- Multi-factor authentication (TOTP, SMS)
- Session management with secure tokens
- Automatic session expiration (7 days)
- Device tracking and management
- Suspicious activity detection

**Password Requirements:**
- Minimum 8 characters
- At least one uppercase letter
- At least one lowercase letter
- At least one number
- At least one special character
- Common password blacklist
- Password strength indicator

**Security Measures:**
- bcrypt password hashing (cost factor 10)
- JWT tokens with RS256 signing
- httpOnly, secure cookies
- CSRF token protection
- Rate limiting on auth endpoints (5 attempts per 15 minutes)
- Account lockout after 10 failed attempts

### 13.2 Authorization

**Role-Based Access Control:**

| Role | Projects | Collaborators | Deployments | Settings |
|------|----------|---------------|-------------|----------|
| Owner | Full control | Manage | Create/View | Full |
| Editor | Edit | View | Create/View | View |
| Viewer | View only | View | View | View |

**API Authorization:**
- All API requests require valid JWT
- Token validation on every request
- Scope-based permissions
- Resource ownership verification

### 13.3 Data Protection

**Encryption:**
- At-rest: AES-256 encryption for sensitive data
- In-transit: TLS 1.3 for all connections
- Database: Supabase encrypted backups
- Secrets: Environment variables encrypted

**PII Handling:**
- Minimal data collection
- User consent for all data usage
- Right to access (GDPR Article 15)
- Right to erasure (GDPR Article 17)
- Data portability (GDPR Article 20)
- Retention policy: 90 days after account deletion

**Secrets Management:**
- API keys stored encrypted
- Environment variables per deployment
- Automatic secret rotation (quarterly)
- No secrets in code or Git
- Audit log for secret access

### 13.4 Input Validation

**All Inputs Must:**
- Be validated on client and server
- Use Zod schemas for type safety
- Sanitize HTML to prevent XSS
- Use parameterized queries (no string concatenation)
- Have length limits
- Check file types and sizes (uploads)
- Validate image dimensions (uploads)

**Example Validation:**

```typescript
import { z } from 'zod';

const projectSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string()
    .min(3, 'Name must be at least 3 characters')
    .max(100, 'Name must not exceed 100 characters')
    .regex(/^[a-zA-Z0-9\s-_]+$/, 'Name contains invalid characters'),
  
  description: z.string()
    .max(500, 'Description must not exceed 500 characters')
    .optional(),
  
  uiKit: z.enum([
    'modern-minimalist',
    'bold-colorful',
    'corporate-professional'
  ])
});

// Usage
const validateProject = (data: unknown) => {
  try {
    return projectSchema.parse(data);
  } catch (error) {
    if (error instanceof z.ZodError) {
      throw new ValidationError(error.errors);
    }
    throw error;
  }
};
```

### 13.5 Rate Limiting

**Limits:**
- Anonymous: 10 requests/minute, 100/hour
- Authenticated: 100 requests/minute, 1000/hour
- API Key: 1000 requests/minute, 10000/hour
- Deployment: 10 per hour
- Code generation: 20 per hour

**Implementation:**
```typescript
import { rateLimit } from '@/lib/rate-limit';

const limiter = rateLimit({
  interval: 60 * 1000, // 1 minute
  uniqueTokenPerInterval: 500 // Max 500 users per interval
});

export async function middleware(req: Request) {
  const identifier = req.headers.get('x-forwarded-for') || 'anonymous';
  
  try {
    await limiter.check(identifier, 100); // 100 requests per minute
  } catch {
    return new Response('Rate limit exceeded', { status: 429 });
  }
  
  return NextResponse.next();
}
```

### 13.6 Security Headers

**Required Headers:**
```
Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' 'unsafe-eval'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: https:; font-src 'self' data:; connect-src 'self' https://*.supabase.co;
X-Frame-Options: DENY
X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block
Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(self)
Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload
```

### 13.7 Vulnerability Management

**Process:**
1. **Detection:**
   - Automated dependency scanning (npm audit)
   - Dependabot alerts
   - Weekly vulnerability reports

2. **Assessment:**
   - Severity rating (Critical, High, Medium, Low)
   - Exploitability analysis
   - Impact assessment

3. **Remediation:**
   - Critical: Patch within 24 hours
   - High: Patch within 7 days
   - Medium: Patch within 30 days
   - Low: Patch in next release

4. **Verification:**
   - Test fixes in staging
   - Deploy to production
   - Verify fix effectiveness
   - Update security documentation

**Tools:**
- npm audit (dependencies)
- Snyk (vulnerability scanning)
- GitHub Security Advisories
- OWASP ZAP (penetration testing)

---

## 14. Performance Requirements

### 14.1 Frontend Performance

**Requirements:**

| Metric | Target | Measurement |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| Initial Load | < 3s | Time to Interactive (TTI) |
| Canvas Render | < 2s | First Contentful Paint |
| Component Drag | 60 FPS | Frame rate during interaction |
| Property Update | < 100ms | Time from input to UI update |
| Code Generation | < 5s | For typical project (50 components) |
| Preview Mode | < 1s | Time to render preview |
| Save Operation | < 500ms | Time to save to database |

**Optimization Strategies:**
- Code splitting (per route)
- Lazy loading (components)
- Image optimization (Next.js Image)
- Virtualization (large lists)
- Memoization (React.memo, useMemo)
- Debouncing (auto-save, search)
- Service worker (offline mode)
- CDN (static assets)

**Bundle Size Targets:**
- Initial JS: < 300KB (gzipped)
- Total JS: < 1MB (gzipped)
- CSS: < 50KB (gzipped)
- Fonts: < 100KB total

### 14.2 Backend Performance

**Requirements:**

| Endpoint | Target | P95 | P99 |
|----------|--------|-----|-----|
| GET /api/projects | < 200ms | 300ms | 500ms |
| POST /api/projects | < 500ms | 800ms | 1s |
| GET /api/components | < 100ms | 150ms | 200ms |
| POST /api/generate/web | < 5s | 8s | 10s |
| POST /api/deploy/web | < 30s | 45s | 60s |
| POST /api/deploy/ota | < 30s | 45s | 60s |

**Database Performance:**
- Query time: < 100ms (P95)
- Connection pool: 20 connections
- Query timeout: 10s
- Index all foreign keys
- Use EXPLAIN ANALYZE for complex queries

**Caching Strategy:**
- Redis for session data (TTL: 7 days)
- CDN for static assets (TTL: 1 year)
- Browser cache for generated code (TTL: 1 hour)
- Database query cache (TTL: 5 minutes)

### 14.3 Mobile Performance

**Requirements:**

| Metric | iOS | Android |
|--------|-----|---------|
| App Size | < 30MB | < 40MB |
| Startup Time | < 3s | < 4s |
| Frame Rate | 60 FPS | 60 FPS |
| Memory Usage | < 150MB | < 200MB |
| Battery Impact | Low | Low |

**Optimization:**
- Use React Native's optimization
- Lazy load screens
- Optimize images (WebP)
- Minimize re-renders
- Use Hermes engine
- Remove console.log in production

### 14.4 Scalability Requirements

**Concurrent Users:**
- Phase 1: 1,000 concurrent users
- Phase 2: 10,000 concurrent users
- Phase 3: 100,000 concurrent users

**Infrastructure:**
- Horizontal scaling (add more instances)
- Database read replicas
- Load balancing (round-robin)
- Auto-scaling based on CPU/memory
- Geographic distribution (multi-region)

**Database:**
- Connection pooling
- Query optimization
- Proper indexing
- Partitioning (for large tables)
- Archiving old data

