## 18. Accessibility Requirements

### 18.1 WCAG 2.1 Level AA Compliance

**Perceivable:**
- All images have alt text
- Videos have captions
- Color contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1 (text)
- Color contrast ratio ≥ 3:1 (UI components)
- Text can be resized up to 200%
- No information conveyed by color alone

**Operable:**
- All functionality keyboard accessible
- Keyboard focus visible
- No keyboard traps
- Skip links present
- Descriptive link text
- Multiple ways to navigate

**Understandable:**
- Page language declared
- Consistent navigation
- Consistent identification
- Error identification
- Error suggestions
- Labels for form inputs

**Robust:**
- Valid HTML
- ARIA labels where needed
- Name, role, value for all UI components
- Status messages announced

### 18.2 Keyboard Navigation

**Shortcuts:**
- Tab: Navigate forward
- Shift + Tab: Navigate backward
- Enter/Space: Activate button/link
- Arrow keys: Navigate within component
- Escape: Close modal/dialog
- / or Ctrl+K: Search/command palette

**Focus Management:**
- Visible focus indicator (2px outline)
- Logical tab order
- Focus trapped in modals
- Focus returned after closing modal
- Skip to main content link

### 18.3 Screen Reader Support

**Requirements:**
- All interactive elements have accessible names
- ARIA landmarks (header, nav, main, footer)
- ARIA live regions for dynamic updates
- Form labels and error messages
- Button states (disabled, pressed, expanded)
- Progress indicators

**Testing:**
- NVDA (Windows)
- JAWS (Windows)
- VoiceOver (macOS, iOS)
- TalkBack (Android)

