## 19. Internationalization

### 19.1 Supported Languages (v1.0)

**Launch Languages:**
- English (en)
- Spanish (es)
- French (fr)
- German (de)
- Portuguese (pt)
- Chinese Simplified (zh-CN)
- Japanese (ja)

**Future Languages:**
- Arabic (ar)
- Hindi (hi)
- Russian (ru)
- Italian (it)
- Korean (ko)

### 19.2 Implementation

**Framework:**
- next-intl (Next.js)
- react-i18next (React Native)

**Translation Files:**
```typescript
// locales/en/common.json
{
  "nav": {
    "home": "Home",
    "builder": "Builder",
    "projects": "Projects"
  },
  "button": {
    "save": "Save",
    "cancel": "Cancel",
    "publish": "Publish"
  },
  "project": {
    "create": "Create Project",
    "name": "Project Name",
    "description": "Description"
  }
}

// Usage
import { useTranslations } from 'next-intl';

function MyComponent() {
  const t = useTranslations('common');
  
  return (
    <button>{t('button.save')}</button>
  );
}
```

### 19.3 Localization

**Date/Time:**
- Use Intl.DateTimeFormat
- Show in user's timezone
- 24-hour vs 12-hour based on locale

**Numbers:**
- Use Intl.NumberFormat
- Decimal separator based on locale
- Currency formatting

**Text Direction:**
- LTR (left-to-right): Most languages
- RTL (right-to-left): Arabic, Hebrew

