## 20. Analytics & Monitoring

### 20.1 Product Analytics

**Events to Track:**

**User Events:**
- Sign Up
- Sign In
- Project Created
- Component Added
- Function Attached
- Module Installed
- Project Published
- Deployment Completed

**Engagement Metrics:**
- Daily Active Users (DAU)
- Weekly Active Users (WAU)
- Monthly Active Users (MAU)
- Retention (D1, D7, D30)
- Session duration
- Projects per user
- Components per project

**Conversion Metrics:**
- Sign up → First project: 80%
- First project → First publish: 60%
- Free → Paid (ecosystem): 5%

**Tools:**
- PostHog (product analytics)
- Google Analytics 4 (web traffic)
- Mixpanel (user behavior)

### 20.2 Error Tracking

**Sentry Configuration:**
```typescript
import * as Sentry from '@sentry/nextjs';

Sentry.init({
  dsn: process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN,
  environment: process.env.NODE_ENV,
  tracesSampleRate: 0.1, // 10% of transactions
  beforeSend(event, hint) {
    // Scrub sensitive data
    if (event.request) {
      delete event.request.cookies;
      delete event.request.headers['authorization'];
    }
    return event;
  }
});
```

**Error Handling:**
- Catch all errors
- Log context (user, project, component)
- Show user-friendly message
- Send to Sentry
- Alert on critical errors

### 20.3 Performance Monitoring

**Web Vitals:**
- Largest Contentful Paint (LCP): < 2.5s
- First Input Delay (FID): < 100ms
- Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS): < 0.1
- First Contentful Paint (FCP): < 1.8s
- Time to Interactive (TTI): < 3.8s

**Custom Metrics:**
- Canvas render time
- Code generation time
- Deployment time
- Function execution time

**Tools:**
- Vercel Analytics (Web Vitals)
- Lighthouse CI (automated audits)
- Chrome DevTools (manual testing)

