## 24. Risk Management

### 24.1 Technical Risks

| Risk | Impact | Probability | Mitigation |
|------|--------|-------------|------------|
| Supabase outage | High | Low | Backup provider ready, local development |
| Vercel rate limits | Medium | Medium | AWS fallback, contact Vercel for limits |
| Code generation bugs | High | Medium | Extensive testing, gradual rollout |
| Mobile build failures | Medium | Medium | Fallback to manual builds, clear errors |
| Database performance | High | Low | Monitoring, query optimization, caching |
| Security breach | Critical | Low | Security audits, bug bounty, rapid response |

### 24.2 Business Risks

| Risk | Impact | Probability | Mitigation |
|------|--------|-------------|------------|
| Low user adoption | Critical | Medium | Marketing, community building, SEO |
| Competitor copies | Medium | High | Stay ahead with innovation, community |
| Funding shortage | High | Low | Keep costs low, donations, ecosystem revenue |
| Key person dependency | Medium | Medium | Documentation, knowledge sharing |
| Legal challenges | High | Low | Legal review, proper licensing, T&C |
| Community toxicity | Medium | Low | Code of conduct, moderation, clear guidelines |

### 24.3 Contingency Plans

**If user growth is slow:**
- Increase marketing efforts
- Improve onboarding flow
- Add more tutorials
- Engage with communities (Reddit, Twitter)
- Partner with influencers

**If technical issues arise:**
- Emergency response team
- Clear communication to users
- Rollback procedures
- Post-mortem analysis
- Preventive measures

**If funding runs out:**
- Accelerate marketplace launch
- Seek donations (Open Collective)
- Consider limited paid tiers (enterprise)
- Partner with related companies
- Apply for grants (open source)

